race.comment: THE CRIMSON PIRATE (14) missed last start in this grade, sustaining a long run from the back of the pack as a $4.40 chance. That effort rates highly and the rise to 1800m now doesn't look an issue. He remains down in the weights and if he can settle a touch closer this time around, he can go one better. MISSISSIPPI DAWN (15) looks well placed here on recent efforts, sticking on strongly from well back to be 1.4L off the winner at the finish. That form has already been franked and she draws a much better gate this time around. Gets an opportunity to sit closer this time around and that can see her hard to hold out. SUMMER'S LEGACY (6) made it back-to-back wins last start when getting her nose down right on the post. Pike remains in the saddle and while the barrier is a niggle, she looks a progressive type. MAGNA'S CHOICE (7) went 1200 to 1800m last start and wasn't beaten far. He'll be better for that effort. BATTLE COMMANDER (3) is racing well and has to be included.
